atg.search.query.formhandlers
Class XMLTagBuilderVisitor

java.lang.Object
  atg.search.query.formhandlers.TagBuilder
      atg.search.query.formhandlers.XMLTagBuilderVisitor
All Implemented Interfaces:
HashMapMapVisitor
public class XMLTagBuilderVisitor
extends TagBuilder
implements HashMapMapVisitor

This class recursively visits a map that may contain other maps and from the HashMap data builds one or more XML tags. The hashmaps have keys that are strings and values that are either strings or other hashmaps. The recognized keys include:

  • "tagname" - The presence of this key and its associated string value indicates the beginning of a tag.
  • "attr" - This optional key should reference a map which contains the key/value pairs representing the attributes for this tag
  • "body" - This optional key contains the tag's body, i.e. the text between <tagname></tagname>
  • "__generate" - If this value is either null or "true", this visitor will generate this tag. Otherwise it will not. This value is set by the XMLPreProcessorVisitor.
